# Windsurf Rules for SlotSmart

## Project Context

Project: SlotSmart
Type: SaaS Web Application - Tennis Club Management
Tech Stack: ASP.NET Core (.NET 10), React, TypeScript, Material UI, Entity Framework Core, PostgreSQL

## AI Framework Integration

This project uses the Supervisor-Worker AI Framework.
- Framework location: docs/SUPERVISOR/
- Always check CURRENT-STATUS.md before major work
- Follow role protocols (SUPERVISOR or WORKER)

## Core Rules

### Architecture
- Clean Architecture: Domain → Application → Infrastructure → Presentation
- Domain layer has NO dependency on Infrastructure
- Use DTOs for all API contracts
- Multi-tenant isolation: always filter by ClubId

### C# Standards
- Async/await throughout (no .Result or .Wait())
- UUIDv7 for all entity identifiers
- Dependency injection for all dependencies
- Validate all inputs

### TypeScript Standards
- Strict TypeScript (no `any`)
- Functional React components with hooks
- Separate API services from UI components

### Testing
- TDD: failing test first, then implementation
- Test command: `dotnet test`
- 80%+ coverage for business logic

### Documentation
- Update CHANGELOG.md after changes
- Keep docs/SUPERVISOR/CURRENT-STATUS.md current

## Session Protocol

Start: Read docs/SUPERVISOR/CURRENT-STATUS.md
End: Update CURRENT-STATUS and CHANGELOG if code changed

